The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe. This white hockey mask and floral shirt were popular choices during his Vice phase. Got my hair combed back and my sunglasses on.

A notorious rebel and brilliant improviser, Vypa is one of twelve sisters born into poverty and left to fend for themselves at the age of seven. Vypa's solo attacks against her country's military dictatorship were so prolific the military assumed her work was the result of a small team of people. At one point, Vypa mistook a remote Guerrilla Warfare (GW) training ground for a government outpost. Shortly after invoking one of her infamous 'sting and choke' maneuvers on the camp she realized her mistake, but not before she had Capt. Crasswater tied up to a tree and threatened at knife point. Impressed and a little frightened, Crasswater recruited Vypa and her sisters into the GW. Together they now lead all jungle-based GW missions and 'government awareness' campaigns. Don't worry, it's just me.

She excels in her human aquatic potential and her skill as an elite marksman and soldier. 'Goggles' earned her nickname when a bullet struck her left eye—or would have—if it weren't for 'Wet Sox' reminding her to grab her full kit 'for the last time!' Despite her occasional forgetfulness, Cmdr. Fernandez is one of two elite combat diver SEALs to be awarded The Navy Cross for classified underwater operations. Be still my beating heart.

A cheap option for cash-strapped players, the FAMAS effectively fills the niche between more expensive rifles and the less-effective SMGs. A hand painted mechanized owl sits atop a nest of orange and brown feathers. +1 to Wisdom

Manufactured in Switzerland, the cutting-edge MP9 SMG is an ergonomic polymer weapon favored by private security firms. It has been painted white and given a stark red magazine. Perfect for shooting toasters

With a smaller magazine than its unmuffled counterpart, the silenced M4A1 provides quieter shots with less recoil and better accuracy. A custom paint job depicting a frightening nocturnal visitor has been applied. Next time set an alarm
Sticker: Unicorn

The R8 Revolver delivers a highly accurate and powerful round at the expense of a lengthy trigger-pull. Firing rapidly by fanning the hammer may be the best option when point-blank stopping power is required. Its ivory handle is paired with ornate, engraved flourishes on blue metalwork. Pull the lever
Versatile but expensive, the German-made MP7 SMG is the perfect choice for high-impact close-range combat. It has been covered in white logo decals over a red and black hydrographic. Space for rent
Sticker: First Blood

Firing two large-mag Berettas at once will lower accuracy and increase load times. On the bright side, you'll get to fire two large-mag Berettas at once. Between the green dyed pearl handled grips, gryphon side plates, and laser etched slide; these pistols redefine elegance. Face off and release the doves

The XM1014 is a powerful fully automatic shotgun that justifies its heftier price tag with the ability to paint a room with lead fast. A custom paint job resembling a gator spitting fire has been applied. Boom. Bam. Bop... Pow.

This sticker can be applied to any weapon you own and can be scraped to look more worn. You can scrape the same sticker multiple times, making it a bit more worn each time, until it is removed from the weapon.

Easily recognizable for its unique bullpup design, the P90 is a great weapon to shoot on the move due to its high-capacity magazine and low recoil. The wooden stock has been hand-carved, sanded, and laminated. Tweezers not included

A less expensive option among the terrorist-exclusive assault rifles, the Galil AR is a serviceable weapon in medium to long-range combat. It has been hand-painted and distressed. The skull painted over the dust cover appears to chatter when the bolt reciprocates. Some say that when you laugh, the world laughs with you...but when Chatterbox laughs there are only screams

Highly accurate and armor-piercing, the pricy Five-Seven is a slow-loader that compensates with a generous 20-round magazine and forgiving recoil. A silver flame on the muzzle overlays a purple base with a metal flake finish. Element detected: Cs

More accurate but less damaging than its AK-47 counterpart, the M4A4 is the full-auto assault rifle of choice for CTs. It has been custom painted with a sci-fi design. Anyone can predict the future... a visionary shapes it

This is a commemorative IEM 2019 Katowice CS:GO Major Championship Coin which tracks your progress throughout the event, provides full access to the Katowice 2019 Pick'Em Challenge, exclusive access to Souvenir Packages, Steam.tv chat flairs, and unlimited team graffiti for the duration of the event.

You can upgrade your Katowice 2019 Coin by completing challenges. You can redeem a Souvenir Package every time you upgrade your Coin.
Awarded for outstanding service and achievement in 2019.
This item commemorates the 2016 ESL One Cologne CS:GO Championship.
It was dropped during the Quarterfinal match between Natus Vincere and Team Liquid, and autographed by Ioann Sukhariev who was the most valuable player in that round.

The CT-exclusive Mag-7 delivers a devastating amount of damage at close range. Its rapid magazine-style reloads make it a great tactical choice. It has been spray-painted with radiological warning hazard patterns.
Sticker: Natus Vincere (Gold) | Cologne 2016, Edward (Gold) | Cologne 2016, Team Liquid (Gold) | Cologne 2016, ESL (Gold) | Cologne 2016

This badge commemorates loyal membership in the Counter-Strike community prior to the Danger Zone update. Strength through loyalty.
